        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 12:06PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1206 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles west of Latexo to near Sebastopol to
near Goodrich. Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crockett, Livingston, Austonio, Apple Springs, Trinity, Onalaska,
Corrigan, Grapeland, Groveton, Lovelady, Kennard, Latexo, Goodrich,
Seven Oaks, Sebastopol, Lake Livingston State Park, Alabama-Coushatta
Reservation, West Livingston, Leggett, and Pennington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
